article.headline: Ball St. 72, E. Illinois 59
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- Jarrod Jones had 21 points and 13 rebounds Saturday in Ball State's 72-59 season-opening victory over Eastern Illinois. The Cardinals jumped to a 23-6 lead in the first 8 minutes of the game, took their biggest lead at 37-18 on a layup by Jones late in the first half and coasted the rest of the way until a late rally in the game's closing minutes. Eastern pulled within 60-54 with 3 minutes to go before a basket by Anthony Newell started an 8-0 run that put the game out of reach. Newell finished with 19 points. Eastern was led by Roman Martin with 17 points. .
